{"questionId":"21889","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two schools are represented by points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>)</mo></math> on the graph below. A road,&nbsp;represented by the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> with equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>−</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, passes near the schools. An architect&nbsp;is asked to determine the location of a new bus stop on the road such that it is the same&nbsp;distance from the two schools.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ad53c9062d4530748084d1ba1030bd2d45cb7359.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>[AB]</mtext></math> . Give your equation in the&nbsp;form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>gradient&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>midpoint&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>22</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>gradient of bisector&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mtext>gradient&nbsp;AB</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>perpendicular bisector:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>22</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>perpendicular bisector:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>46</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21889","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.6a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the perpendicular bisector of [AB] . Give your equation in the form y=mx+c.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}